Gould, 1859, by original designation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="39" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Shell oblique-heliciform to ovate and last whorl deflected. Penultimate whorl round to bluntly angular and extended beyond last whorl. Apertural dentition includes only one parietal lamella. Genitalia with penial sheath thin to thick and extending ~ 1/2 to entire penis length. Penial hooks dense, slightly expanded at base, tips pointed, located on low to high conical papillae and vaginal hooks absent.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="39" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39">
<taxonomicName authorityName="von Moellendorff" authorityYear="1906" class="Gastropoda" family="Streptaxidae" genus="Haploptychius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haploptychius" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Haploptychius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is almost identical with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Siriboon &amp; Panha" authorityYear="2014" class="Gastropoda" family="Streptaxidae" genus="Carinartemis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carinartemis" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Carinartemis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a deflected last whorl, extended penultimate whorl, and bearing a single parietal lamella. However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="von Moellendorff" authorityYear="1906" class="Gastropoda" family="Streptaxidae" genus="Haploptychius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haploptychius" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Haploptychius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be recognized by its oblique-ovate shell and rounded to angular penultimate whorl, while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Siriboon &amp; Panha" authorityYear="2014" class="Gastropoda" family="Streptaxidae" genus="Carinartemis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carinartemis" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Carinartemis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possesses an oblique-heliciform shell with sharply keeled penultimate whorl. In genitalia, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="von Moellendorff" authorityYear="1906" class="Gastropoda" family="Streptaxidae" genus="Haploptychius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haploptychius" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Haploptychius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has long and slender penial hooks, without vaginal hooks, while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Siriboon &amp; Panha" authorityYear="2014" class="Gastropoda" family="Streptaxidae" genus="Carinartemis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carinartemis" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Carinartemis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possesses shorter and blunt penial hooks, and sometimes transparent vaginal hooks may be present (
<bibRefCitation author="Siriboon, T" journalOrPublisher="The Raffles Bulletin of Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" pagination="161 - 174" refId="B77" refString="Siriboon, T, Sutcharit, C, Naggs, F, Rowson, B, Panha, S, 2014b. Revision of the carnivorous snail genus Indoartemon Forcart, 1946 and a new genus Carinartemis from Thailand (Pulmonata: Streptaxidae). The Raffles Bulletin of Zoology 62: 161 - 174" title="Revision of the carnivorous snail genus Indoartemon Forcart, 1946 and a new genus Carinartemis from Thailand (Pulmonata: Streptaxidae)." volume="62" year="2014 b">Siriboon et al. 2014b</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.589.7933" author="Inkhavilay, K" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" pagination="23 - 53" refId="B35" refString="Inkhavilay, K, Siriboon, T, Sutcharit, C, Rowson, B, Panha, S, 2016. The first revision of the carnivorous land snail family Streptaxidae in Laos, with description of three new species (Pulmonata, Stylommatophora, Streptaxidae). ZooKeys 589: 23 - 53, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.589.7933" title="The first revision of the carnivorous land snail family Streptaxidae in Laos, with description of three new species (Pulmonata, Stylommatophora, Streptaxidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.589.7933" volume="589" year="2016">Inkhavilay et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39">
A recent molecular phylogeny revealed that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="von Moellendorff" authorityYear="1906" class="Gastropoda" family="Streptaxidae" genus="Haploptychius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haploptychius" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Haploptychius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is polyphyletic, and the traditional genus concept using shell shape and apertural dentition seems unreliable (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/14772000.2020.1783384" author="Siriboon, T" journalOrPublisher="Systematics and Biodiversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" pagination="720 - 738" refId="B78" refString="Siriboon, T, Naggs, F, Wade, CM, Jeratthitikul, E, Tongkerd, P, Jirapatrasilp, P, Panha, S, Sutcharit, C, 2020. Phylogenetic relationships of the carnivorous terrestrial snail family Streptaxidae (Stylommatophora: Achatinina) in Thailand and surrounding areas of Southeast Asia. Systematics and Biodiversity 18 (7): 720 - 738, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/14772000.2020.1783384" title="Phylogenetic relationships of the carnivorous terrestrial snail family Streptaxidae (Stylommatophora: Achatinina) in Thailand and surrounding areas of Southeast Asia." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/14772000.2020.1783384" volume="18" year="2020">Siriboon et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
). However, further intensive genital examination and molecular analysis of the type species are necessary to restrict the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="von Moellendorff" authorityYear="1906" class="Gastropoda" family="Streptaxidae" genus="Haploptychius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haploptychius" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Haploptychius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s.s., and generic revision absolutely requires both forms of evidence. Therefore, since the morphological and molecular evidence have never been evaluated, we follow the traditional genus concept in recognizing the streptaxids with oblique-heliciform shells and only one parietal lamella as members of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="von Moellendorff" authorityYear="1906" class="Gastropoda" family="Streptaxidae" genus="Haploptychius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haploptychius" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Haploptychius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s.l.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39">
Currently, the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="von Moellendorff" authorityYear="1906" class="Gastropoda" family="Streptaxidae" genus="Haploptychius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haploptychius" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Haploptychius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is comprised of about 40 nominal species distributed from India to Indochina, southern and central China, and Sulawesi of Indonesia (
<bibRefCitation author="Kobelt, W" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Society for Bibliography of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" refId="B37" refString="Kobelt, W, 1905. Die Raublungenschnecken (Agnatha). Zweite Abtheilung: Streptaxidae und Daudebardiidae. Systematisches Conchylien-Cabinet von Martini und Chemnitz 1(12b) (2): 1-211 pls42-71 [pp. 1-96 pls 42-59 (1905) ; 97-211, pls 60-71 (1906)]." title="Die Raublungenschnecken (Agnatha). Zweite Abtheilung: Streptaxidae und Daudebardiidae. Systematisches Conchylien-Cabinet von Martini und Chemnitz 1 (12 b) (2): 1 - 211 pls 42 - 71 [pp. 1 - 96 pls 42 - 59 (1905); 97 - 211, pls 60 - 71 (1906)]." year="1905">Kobelt 1906</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.13103" author="Blanford, WT" journalOrPublisher="Taylor and Francis, London" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" refId="B10" refString="Blanford, WT, Godwin-Austen, HH, 1908. The Fauna of British India, Including Ceylon and Burma. Mollusca. Testacellidae and Zonitidae. Taylor and Francis, London, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.13103" title="The Fauna of British India, Including Ceylon and Burma. Mollusca. Testacellidae and Zonitidae." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.13103" year="1908">Blanford and Godwin-Austen 1908</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Zilch, A" journalOrPublisher="Archiv fuer Molluskenkunde" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" pagination="79 - 120" refId="B100" refString="Zilch, A, 1961. Die Typen und Typoide des Natur-Museums Senckenberg 24: Mollusca, Streptaxidae. Archiv fuer Molluskenkunde 90: 79 - 120" title="Die Typen und Typoide des Natur-Museums Senckenberg 24: Mollusca, Streptaxidae." volume="90" year="1961">Zilch 1961</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Richardson, L" journalOrPublisher="Tryonia" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" pagination="1 - 326" refId="B70" refString="Richardson, L, 1988. Streptaxacea: Catalog of species, Part I, Streptaxidae. Tryonia 16: 1 - 326" title="Streptaxacea: Catalog of species, Part I, Streptaxidae." volume="16" year="1988">Richardson 1988</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Schileyko, AA" journalOrPublisher="Zoologica Scripta" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" refId="B73" refString="Schileyko, AA, 2000. Treatise on recent terrestrial pulmonate molluscs: Rhytididae, Chlamydephoridae, Systrophiidae, Haplotrematidae, Streptaxidae, Spiraxidae, Oleacinidae, Testacellidae. Ruthenica (Supplement 2 Part 6): 731-880." title="Treatise on recent terrestrial pulmonate molluscs: Rhytididae, Chlamydephoridae, Systrophiidae, Haplotrematidae, Streptaxidae, Spiraxidae, Oleacinidae, Testacellidae. Ruthenica (Supplement 2 Part 6): 731 - 880." year="2000">Schileyko 2000</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Do, DS" journalOrPublisher="Ruthenica" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" pagination="37 - 43" refId="B19" refString="Do, DS, Do, VN, 2015. The terrestrial snail family Streptaxidae J. Gray, 1860 (Gastropoda: Pulmonata) from Son La, Vietnam, with description of two new species. Ruthenica 25: 37 - 43" title="The terrestrial snail family Streptaxidae J. Gray, 1860 (Gastropoda: Pulmonata) from Son La, Vietnam, with description of two new species." volume="25" year="2015">Do and Do 2015</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.589.7933" author="Inkhavilay, K" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" pagination="23 - 53" refId="B35" refString="Inkhavilay, K, Siriboon, T, Sutcharit, C, Rowson, B, Panha, S, 2016. The first revision of the carnivorous land snail family Streptaxidae in Laos, with description of three new species (Pulmonata, Stylommatophora, Streptaxidae). ZooKeys 589: 23 - 53, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.589.7933" title="The first revision of the carnivorous land snail family Streptaxidae in Laos, with description of three new species (Pulmonata, Stylommatophora, Streptaxidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.589.7933" volume="589" year="2016">Inkhavilay et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
). In addition, five species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="von Moellendorff" authorityYear="1906" class="Gastropoda" family="Streptaxidae" genus="Haploptychius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haploptychius" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Haploptychius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s.l. have been documented mainly in southeastern Myanmar (
